  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Increased forex earnings: The project will help increase forex earnings of the apparel industry and improve the currently the country&apos;&apos;s Balance of Payments. 2. Job creation: The project will lead to increased employment opportunities, and in particular, female employment, in Sri Lanka.  3. Demonstration Effect: The project will support one of Sri Lanka&apos;&apos;s premium apparel sector players in terms of E&amp;S compliance, OHS standards, and energy efficiency thereby setting the industry benchmark.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MAS Capital (Pvt) Ltd is a vertically integrated intimate-wear and active-wear manufacturing group headquartered out of Sri Lanka. The groups operations span the entire value chain of the manufacturing process from fabric, elastic, lace and accessories to the final product. The proposed project is new investment for capacity expansions, sustainability projects and product development at MAS Capital (Pvt) Ltd, MAS Active (Pvt) Ltd, Trischel (Pvt) Ltd and Textprint Lanka (Pvt) Ltd (collectively the Co-borrowers) and their subsidiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
